This is the ultimate rabbit / squirrel gun.  It is a Savage 24f in .22lr upper and 20 gauge lower with 3.0" chamber.  Overall it is Fair+ to Good condition.  The bluing is good+ on the barrels and fair+ to good on the receiver -- but the wood is not pretty.  I'll tell you that right now.... this is not a gun you buy for aesthetics.  What makes it special are the customizations:  (1) Both barrels shortened from 24" down to EIGHTEEN (18.1) inches, for the ultimate short light handy small game gun; this is a professional cut / crown / re-blue, & sight setback job by Jared McCluskey (McCluskey machine shop) out of Altus, and (2) Stock shortened - the LOP went from about 14.5" to about 13.5", and (3) Good professional trigger job - was up close to 14 lbs (not kidding); now it breaks cleanly at 5 lbs, 9 oz.  Great bores in both barrels.  Fixed choke on the shotgun barrel - due to being shortened, it's effectively a cylinder bore - quail, dove, squirrel and rabbit type bore for < 25 yards.

title: For Sale:  FN Scar 17S FDE NIB
postcontent:
Fraud Alert / Scam Alert / CAUTION!

Fraudsters are attempting to sell sought-after firearms by copying electronic data from legitimate postings and referencing, unbeknownst to their knowledge, local FFL dealer's information in their geographic areas of "fraud operation" in an attempt to both legitimize and entice victims to purchase firearms from them.

Copy the picture in the ad and use Google Chrome to conduct an Internet search of the image(s) they are using.  You may find the image on other actionable websites where the firearm has already been sold at a much higher price!  Contact the alleged FFL dealer they reference in their emails and ask if they know the selling party.  Ask for additional pictures!  Advise the seller that you live in the local area and you would like to make an appointment to inspect the firearm in person!  Deal with FFL dealers directly and they should help be able to attest to the legitimacy of the transaction and verify the firearm.  

Also, conduct an email review of the internal header's (research the technology using google if you don't know what this is) from the seller and you will be able to identify that the emails are being opened and sent from mobile devices in SOUTH AFRICA!  Do not become a victim of these pirates!  The price may be enticing but do not fall for the scam...  

Also, when you send a cashier's check they cross out the memo portion of the check (identifying the sale of a firearms) and put "N/A" so that it appears you are simply sending them money!  They appear to be using mules in the states to both receive and cash the money using questionable financial centers. 

These fraudsters were selling an FN SCAR 17S FDE NIB with "issued bipod and four FDE magazines" for $2,100.  The total came to $2,175 with shipping from FFL to FFL.  Too good to be true right!  This is a fraud and you should report them to LE authorities.  These pirates need to be caught and prosecuted!  Be alert and don't fall victim... This fraud appears to be proliferating so pass the good word to as many as you can.

title: For Sale/Trade:  m91/30 1934
postcontent:
Nagants in good enough shape to be salvaged were part of the soviets massive refurbishment program following ww2. The primary reasons behind the huge post war overhaul of large, obsolete rifle stockpiles were the anticipation of another impending world war, and the plan to call up seasoned veterans in defense of the motherland. Already familiar with their old mosin nagant rifles and revolvers, those veterans would likely have required very little new training and would easily and rapidly reintegrate into the red machine. 
With the development of newer semi auots that would have required extensive massive retraining, the important issue became of quick mobilization became apearant. However time passed and those great ww2 veterans eventually aged beyond the point of viability. While newer weapons took over the worlds battlefields, the stocks of long outdated ordnance were now imported to the USA. 

This is a pre war 1934 izzy manufacture m90/31 with hexagonal reciever with original russian laminate non refurbished stock. This rifles bore is stone mint shiny chromed out! "Have neer seen one like this" the weapon bears No refurbishment marks or other countrys arsenal markings! The metal has not a mark on it is stone mint! The magazine follower, action etc have no wear! Mint bore. All matching. No refurbishment marks from other countrys !!
This is a very early import that was sold wrapped in brown paper tied in twine. This rifle saw little to no action its entire life, maybe an officers or political gaurds weapon

The rifles antiquated lines, and historical signifigance is something to be sought after for years to come. This rifle was made well when an individuals workmanship was apreciated and one took pride in what they did. It also was a matter of national pride, a "we made it here" battle rifle.

title: For Sale:  ***PRICE REDUCED 2ND AND LAST TIME***:  DPMS LR-260L complete AR10-style rifle, excellent+ condition, with many extras
postcontent:
This is a lightweight AR-10 style, truly all-purpose rifle:  A DPMS LR-260L (in .260 Rem) with 18" barrel, in excellent+ condition.  Note that this is an extremely rare configuration for this rifle (and the best one):  The new LR260Ls if you can get one, have a 20" barrel.  The old ones had an 18" bbl with permanent/fixed muzzle brake. This one has an 18" barrel with no muzzle brake - just 5/8ths x 24 tpi threading for accessory of your choice (and comes with a knurled thread protector).  The barrel is a 1 in 7.5" twist so it will shoot anything you can throw out it, from 140/142 Bergers, Lapuas, & Sierras, to younameit.  Pristine barrel, VERY low round count.  This rifle is very accurate & reliable.  It is the ultimate "just-one" rifle for both SHTF and hunting any game on earth.

The LR260L config is a lightweight hunting config, with ACE skeleton buttstock with recoil pad, lo-pro gas block, and a 2-stage JP enterprises hunting/match trigger - mine has a excellent crisp 5lb, 6oz trigger.

This rifle comes with the following extras/ customizations:
1.  ERGO rubber grip
2.  FAB Industries "T-Grip" front vertical grip with storage compartment, built in switch for light, and comes with a Surefire 6P light 'installed'.
3.  Oversized "Tac-Latch" charging handle
4.   Adjustable gas tube installed, for subsonic or low-power rounds (plus the original gas tube is included)
5.  "Customization" (change from original factory config):  The carbon fiber handguard was replaced with a carbine-length aluminum FF quad-rail of unknown make.  Note that this config results in the gas tube being somewhat exposed due to rifle-length gas system but carbine-length FF handguard.  But this has the added advantage of being able to access and adjust the gas tube adjustment instantly.  This is unusual but to me it was worth it to reduce weight and still have a quad-rail.  It is not a problem however; those gas tubes are steel & tougher than they look and I never hit them on anything.  But if you want to put a longer FF handguard back on here and sell or re-use the FF quad rail , you may of course.  This quad rail cost me about $150 since it's for AR10 not AR15.
